(an+b)y \equiv by \pmod n
(an + b)y = any + by
(an+b)y\equiv 1 \pmod n \iff by \equiv 1 \pmod n
7y \equiv 1 \pmod {18}
7\cdot13y \equiv 13 \pmod{18}\\
7\cdot 13 = 91 = 5\cdot18 + 1
(5\cdot18 + 1)y \equiv 1\pmod{18}
7\cdot13y \equiv 13 \pmod{18} \iff y\equiv 13 \pmod{18}
